This is due to the Bonferroni effect. Bonferroni (1936) shows that type I and type II errors are propagated as multiple hypotheses are tested simultaneously. In general, if α is the desired significance onkdifferent hypotheses being rejected simultaneously, each hypothesis should be tested at (approximately) the
